            <lb/>
12&#xD;<lb/>
He is supposed to say I have spared no labour&#xD;<lb/>
in endeavouring to gain Knowledge - I have seen&#xD;<lb/>
all the great men of my Age. I have&#xD;<lb/>
journeyed through all countries in which I&#xD;<lb/>
had the most distant hope of discovering useful&#xD;<lb/>
truths. I have never been deterred by the&#xD;<lb/>
distance of places nor by dangers nor by&#xD;<lb/>
fears of danger. I have observed the&#xD;<lb/>
various differences of climates - I have&#xD;<lb/>
described the <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">phaen</del> phenomena of the Air&#xD;<lb/>
the Earth and the waters - the fatague&#xD;<lb/>
of body has never disturbed the tranquility&#xD;<lb/>
of my mind and even during my travels&#xD;<lb/>
I have applied my self to quiet meditation&#xD;<lb/>
