                 rend="strikethrough">obsa</del> observations&#xD;<lb/>
upon natural bodies have been preserved&#xD;<lb/>
If we may credit some writers <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag29"
                ref="#person_182"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag29" type="person">
          Democritus
        </name>
            </rs> was&#xD;<lb/>
the first experimental chemist for it is said&#xD;<lb/>
that he was acquainted with methods for bringing&#xD;<lb/>
stone into solution and for ivory -&#xD;<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="16"
                xml:id="pb-16"
                facs="#i16"/>
            <lb/>
14&#xD;<lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
