The other infinitely exccels on account of&#xD;<lb/>
its invincible force and conviction.&#xD;<lb/>
And certain it is that abstruse and profoun<add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">d</add>
            <lb/>
questions in geometry are no where solved by&#xD;<lb/>
a more simple process and upon clearer&#xD;<lb/>
principles than in the writing of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
